{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"The generated function signature matches the expected interface (parameter names, types, return type) specified in the description.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"Signature correctness is partly a model-interpretation problem: a mocked generator can validate checker logic, but it can miss real prompt/model misinterpretations that produce subtly wrong signatures. To catch real failures at this boundary, the test should use a real LLM response path.","test_description":"Run end-to-end generation with a real LLM for several interface-sensitive prompts (including similar parameter names and explicit type requirements). Parse produced code and assert exact signature match against expected interface. Fail if any run returns mismatched names/types/return type.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.05,"Integration":0.25,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.62,"Workflow":0.03}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"The generated implementation passes all provided test cases on the first or a subsequent attempt.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"Passing tests depends on real model output quality across attempts. A pure mock can validate loop control but may hide true failure modes where the model never reaches a correct implementation. Real LLM behavior is required to catch that risk.","test_description":"Use a real LLM and a real execution path for the provided test suite. Assert that the service reports success when at least one attempt (1..3) passes all tests, and that the recorded successful attempt index is correct.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.0,"Integration":0.1,"System":0.15,"Agentic":0.55,"Workflow":0.2}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"When tests fail, the refinement step includes the failure messages in the next LLM prompt so the model can learn from its mistakes.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"This is mainly wiring correctness between test runner output and prompt builder. In-process unit tests can miss serialization/formatting handoff bugs across modules, but real model behavior is not required to verify inclusion of failure text.","test_description":"Wire generator + test executor + prompt-construction modules with a fake LLM client that records prompts. Force attempt 1 to fail with known error text, then assert attempt 2 prompt contains that exact failure content (or required normalized form).","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.25,"Integration":0.7,"System":0.03,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"The service stops after 3 failed attempts and returns a structured error with all three attempts and their test results.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"The real risk is orchestration/state aggregation across retry logic, attempt records, and error shaping. Mocking only a single function can miss cross-module state bugs; real OS/network/model behavior is not required.","test_description":"Run the retry loop with deterministic failing generations/tests for all attempts. Assert exactly 3 attempts were executed, no 4th call occurred, and returned error payload includes three attempt entries with per-attempt test results in the expected schema.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.2,"Integration":0.68,"System":0.07,"Agentic":0.03,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"The full loop — generate, test, refine, test again — produces a working implementation for a function that a single LLM call typically gets wrong.","minimum_level":"Workflow","justification":"This explicitly requires multiple agentic steps in sequence and validates improvement from feedback across iterations. Single-call agentic testing is insufficient because the failure boundary is the multi-step pipeline behavior.","test_description":"Choose a benchmark prompt known to fail in one-shot mode. Execute the real pipeline (attempt 1 fail expected, refinement prompt with failures, subsequent attempt succeeds). Assert final pass plus evidence that success required at least one refine cycle.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.0,"Integration":0.02,"System":0.04,"Agentic":0.12,"Workflow":0.82}}]}
